---
By: Johann W. Goethe
Locus:
  Page: 331
  Verse: 4
Tags:
  - Nature
---
There is no trifling with nature; it is always true, dignified, and just;
it is always in the right, and the faults and errors belong to us. Nature
defies incompetence, but reveals its secrets to the competent, the
truthful, and the pure.
